<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="906" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                    <head>Frohsinn Singing Society</head>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Bern</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-06">May 6, 1865</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <p>The undersigned society, at a full meeting this day, unanimously passed the
                        following resolutions: <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>We cordially approve of the address of sympathy and condolence to
                                the American Union now circulating in this city.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>We order that every member of the society sign his name to this
                                paper, and that it be properly executed. Berne, May 6, 1865. In the
                                name of the Frohsinn Männerchor, of Berne:</item>
                        </list>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>J. HUBER, <hi rend="italic">President</hi>.</item>
                                <item>T. BUCHERT, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>(Eighty-four signatures follow.)</p>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>